@arita37 the advantage of wrapping data preprocessing steps into classes with fit and transform is that: 
1. It will lead to cleaner code ([read why here](https://www.neuraxio.com/en/blog/neuraxle/2019/10/26/neat-machine-learning-pipelines.html)). 
2. It allows for automatic data checkpoints to make your code faster when you run it many times on the same data ([see checkpoint example](https://www.neuraxio.com/en/neuraxle/stable/examples/auto_ml_checkpoint.html)).
